  <front>
   <head>[Epitaph on Sir William Williams]</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Here, foremost in the dangerous paths of fame,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Young Williams fought for England's fair renown;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">His mind each Muse, each Grace adorned his frame,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Nor Envy dared to view him with a frown.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">At Aix uncalled his maiden sword he drew,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">(There first in blood his infant glory sealed);</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">From fortune, pleasure, science, love, he flew,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And scorned repose when Britain took the field.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">With eyes of flame and cool intrepid breast,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Victor he stood on Belle Isle's rocky steeps;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ah gallant youth! this marble tells the rest,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Where melancholy Friendship bends and weeps.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
